[1] Saudi Arabia, 7 new cases, 1 death - MOH 22 Aug 2015
Date: Sat 22 Aug 2015
Source: Saudi Arabia Ministry of Health [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/Statistics-2015-08-22-001.aspx


As of 12:00 noon today, 22 Aug 2015, there have been a total of:
1141 laboratory-confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection, including
487 deaths
592 recoveries and
62 currently active cases including 6 on home isolation

In the past 24 hours there have been:
7 newly confirmed cases
1 newly reported fatality
0 newly reported recoveries

[reported case fatality rate 42.7 percent]

Information on newly confirmed cases:
1- A 63-year-old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker, currently in stable condition. No history of contact with other known cases.

2- A 57-year-old Saudi female, non-healthcare worker, currently in stable condition. Gave a positive history of contact with other known cases.

3- A 41-year-old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker, currently in stable condition. Gave a positive history of contact with other known cases.

4- A 61-year-old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker, currently in stable condition. Gave a positive history of contact with other known cases.

5- A 49-year-old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker, currently in stable condition. Gave a positive history of contact with other known cases.

6- A 27-year-old expat male, healthcare worker, currently in stable condition. Gave a positive history of contact with other known cases.

7- A 26-year-old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker, currently in stable condition. Gave a positive history of contact with other known cases.

Information on newly reported fatality (1 case)

A 63-year-old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker, history of co-morbidities. [Reported as a newly confirmed case on either 11 Aug 2015, 17 Aug 2015, 19 Aug 2015, or 20 Aug 2015 -- the individuals reported on 11, 19 and 20 Aug 2015 were noted to be in critical condition, the individual reported on 17 Aug 2015 was noted to be in stable condition. Those reported on 11 and 17 Aug 2015 were noted to have had contact with known MER-CoV infected cases in the 14 days prior to onset of symptoms, whereas those reported on 19 and 20 Aug 2015 had possible histories of contact with other case(s) that were under review. - Mod.MPP]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[My comment today is essentially the same as yesterday's except with an updating of the numbers of cases reported. Hence, with today's addition of 7 newly confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection all from Riyadh it raises the total number of confirmed cases reported from Riyadh since the beginning of August 2015 to 81 (out of 84 cases reported from all of Saudi Arabia during this period) and the total number of cases reported by Saudi Arabia since June 2012 to 1141, including 487 deaths. One of the cases reported today (no. 6) is in a healthcare worker. Another one of the cases (no. 1) did not give a history of contact with other known case(s) -- like yesterday, the question that arises is whether this is a case reported from another hospital that did not have contact with the King Abdulaziz Medical City hospital in the 14 days prior to onset of his illness. Presumably this information will be available in future update reports from WHO.

Remembering the media report in yesterday's update that mentioned there were an additional 20 suspected cases pending confirmation and possibly additional healthcare workers, if true, we should expect to continue to have more cases reported on a daily basis over the coming days. With the closure of the implicated emergency room and outpatient facilities at the affected hospital, we should start seeing a tapering off of reported cases after an incubation period (14 days) has passed from the time of closure of the facilities.

A map showing the location of the newly reported cases can be found at the source URL above. A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Saudi Arabia can be found at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3596073,131. - Mod.MPP]

